Three killed in soccer dispute in El Salvador . An argument following a local soccer match in El Salvador turned deadly when one of the players set off a hand grenade , killing two and injuring three , including himself , police said on Monday . Tomas Ortiz , 18 , and Francisco Ortiz , 45 , died on Sunday from injuries sustained by the grenade blast , police said . The two were related but officials were unsure how . Police said the grenade was triggered following the Sunday match by Concepcion Miranda , a former army soldier and member of the opposing team . Miranda , who was jailed pending charges , allegedly stole the grenade from an army armory . The argument developed after a victory celebration by one of the teams , police said . 
